# ------------------------------- start overview ------------------------------- # 
    ==> Quick view: Session Hijacking refers to the exploitation of a valid session assigned to a user.
                    the attacker can get the victim's session identifier using a few different methods through
                    typically an XSS is used or bruteforcing.

    ==> session hijack attack:
        - Exploit through XSS.
        - Packet sniffing.
        - Gain direct access to server filesystem where sessions are stored.
        - finding session ID in logs or browser history.
        - session ID is predictable.
# ------------------------------- start overview ------------------------------- # 